race.comment: CAVALLO PARK (8) has not raced since making good late inroads to finish second on debut over 1100m at this track in July. Placed in a recent Randwick trial. The extra 100m this time plays into her hands so a maiden win is on the cards. LETHAL LOVE (11) settled worse than midfield then worked home fairly for third last time out over this course and distance. Will need a little luck from the wide gate but if it comes she is a proper contender. TENNESSEE DOLLY (13) went better than market expectations on debut recently over 1100m here, closing off well to finish fourth. Should take a lot from that run - pity she has drawn so poorly which makes the task all the more difficult. Nothing went right for BRAINIAC (5) at Hawkesbury last start so her effort to be beaten just 1.8 lengths was full of merit. Worth following. OAKFIELD MARS (6) ran a cracker last start over 1000m here and should relish the longer journey third-up.
